<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[264,1323,873,980]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,378,873,899]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Remarks</emphasis>
: The status of 
<taxonomicName box="[550,695,874,899]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Bombylella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auricoma">
<emphasis box="[550,695,874,899]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">B. auricoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not in doubt. It is readily identified as the only species of the genus with predominantly yellow hair and gold depressed hair­like scales on the dorsal surface of the thorax and abdomen.
</paragraph>
